// Device private key and certificate in DER format.
//
// These credentials are generated by your test CA and loaded at boot
// to replace the random ephemeral keypair that mock mode creates.
// This allows the gateway to verify the device cert against the Root CA.
//
// HOW TO GENERATE (using the same CA that produced resonant_root_ca.der):
//
//   1. Generate a device EC private key (P-256):
//        openssl ecparam -genkey -name prime256v1 -noout -out device_key.pem
//
//   2. Create a CSR:
//        openssl req -new -key device_key.pem -out device.csr \
//            -subj "/CN=ResonantDevice001/O=Resonant"
//
//   3. Sign the cert with your Root CA:
//        openssl x509 -req -in device.csr \
//            -CA resonant_root_ca.pem -CAkey resonant_root_ca_key.pem \
//            -CAcreateserial -out device_cert.pem -days 3650 -sha256
//
//   4. Convert both to DER:
//        openssl ec -in device_key.pem -outform DER -out device_key.der
//        openssl x509 -in device_cert.pem -outform DER -out device_cert.der
//
//   5. Convert to C byte arrays:
//        xxd -i device_key.der
//        xxd -i device_cert.der
//
//      Copy the array contents below and update the length constants.

